<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation provides protection against and counteracts the effects of the extra-territorial application of the laws specified in the Annex of this Regulation, including regulations and other legislative instruments, and of actions based thereon or resulting therefrom, where such application affects the interests of persons, referred to in Article 11, engaging in international trade and/or the movement of capital and related commercial activities between the Community and third countries. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rusega n&auml;hakse ette kaitse k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse lisas esitatud seaduste, sealhulgas m&auml;&auml;ruste ja muude &otilde;igusaktide eksterritoriaalse kohaldamise m&otilde;ju eest ja nendel p&otilde;hinevate v&otilde;i neist tulenevate meetmete eest ning selle m&otilde;ju t&otilde;rjumine, kui niisugune kohaldamine m&otilde;jutab artiklis 11 nimetatud isikute huve, kes tegutsevad rahvusvahelises kaubanduses ja/v&otilde;i on seotud kapitali liikumisega ning &uuml;henduse ja kolmandate riikide vahelise &auml;ritegevusega. </eesti>
<inglise> Acting in accordance with the relevant provisions of the Treaty and notwithstanding the provisions of Article 7 (c), the Council may add or delete laws to or from the Annex to this Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> Tegutsedes asutamislepingu asjakohaste s&auml;tete alusel ja olenemata artikli 7 punktist c, v&otilde;ib n&otilde;ukogu k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse lisasse seadusi lisada v&otilde;i neid sealt v&auml;lja j&auml;tta. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> Where the economic and/or financial interests of any person referred to in Article 11 are affected, directly or indirectly, by the laws specified in the Annex or by actions based thereon or resulting therefrom, that person shall inform the Commission accordingly within 30 days from the date on which it obtained such information; insofar as the interests of a legal person are affected, this obligation applies to the directors, managers and other persons with management responsibilities (3). </inglise>
<eesti> Kui artiklis 11 nimetatud isikute majandus- ja/v&otilde;i finantshuve m&otilde;jutavad otseselt v&otilde;i kaudselt lisas m&auml;&auml;ratletud seadused v&otilde;i neil p&otilde;hinevad v&otilde;i neist tulenevad toimingud, teatab nimetatud isik sellest komisjonile 30 p&auml;eva jooksul alates k&otilde;nealuse teabe saamisest; kui m&otilde;jutatakse juriidiliste isikute huve, k&auml;ib see kohustus direktorite, juhatajate ja muude juhtimisvastutusega isikute kohta. (3) </eesti>
<inglise> At the request of the Commission, such person shall provide all information relevant for the purposes of this Regulation in accordance with the request from the Commission within 30 days from the date of the request. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjoni taotlusel esitab see isik kogu k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse seisukohast asjakohase ja komisjoni taotlusele vastava teabe 30 p&auml;eva jooksul taotluse kuup&auml;evast alates. </eesti>
<inglise> All information shall be submitted to the Commission either directly or through the competent authorities of the Member States. Should the information be submitted directly to the Commission, the Commission will inform immediately the competent authorities of the Member States in which the person who gave the information is resident or incorporated. </inglise>
<eesti> Kogu teave edastatakse komisjonile kas otse v&otilde;i liikmesriikide p&auml;devate asutuste kaudu.. Kui teave edastatakse otse komisjonile, teatab komisjon sellest viivitamata selle liikmesriigi p&auml;devatele asutustele, kus teabe esitanud isik elab v&otilde;i on registreeritud. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> All information supplied in accordance with Article 2 shall only be used for the purposes for which it was provided. </inglise>
<eesti> Vastavalt artiklile 2 esitatud teavet kasutatakse ainult selleks, milleks seda n&otilde;uti. </eesti>
<inglise> Information which is by nature confidential or which is provided on a confidential basis shall be covered by the obligation of professional secrecy. </inglise>
<eesti> Konfidentsiaalse v&otilde;i konfidentsiaalselt edastatud teabe kohta kehtib ametisaladuse hoidmise kohustus. </eesti>
<inglise> It shall not be disclosed by the Commission without the express permission of the person providing it. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon ei avalda teavet ilma seda andnud isiku otsese loata; </eesti>
<inglise> Communication of such information shall be permitted where the Commission is obliged or authorized to do so, in particular in connection with legal proceedings. </inglise>
<eesti> Niisuguse teabe edastamist lubatakse, kui komisjon on kohustatud v&otilde;i volitatud seda tegema, eelk&otilde;ige seoses kohtumenetlusega. </eesti>
<inglise> Such communication must take into account the legitimate interests of the person concerned that his or her business secrets should not be divulged. </inglise>
<eesti> Teabe edastamisel tuleb arvesse v&otilde;tta asjaomase isiku &otilde;igustatud huvi, et ei avaldataks tema &auml;risaladusi. </eesti>
<inglise> This Article shall not preclude the disclosure of general information by the Commission. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus ei v&auml;lista &uuml;ldinfo avaldamist komisjoni poolt. </eesti>
<inglise> Such disclosure shall not be permitted if this is incompatible with the original purpose of such information. </inglise>
<eesti> Avaldamist ei lubata, kui see ei ole koosk&otilde;las teabe esitamise esialgse eesm&auml;rgiga. </eesti>
<inglise> In the event of a breach of confidentiality, the originator of the information shall be entitled to obtain that it be deleted, disregarded or rectified, as the case may be. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui rikutakse salastatuse n&otilde;uet, on teabe algsel edastajal &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda, et see olenevalt asjaoludest kas kustutatakse, j&auml;etakse arvesse v&otilde;tmata v&otilde;i korrigeeritakse. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> No judgment of a court or tribunal and no decision of an administrative authority located outside the Community giving effect, directly or indirectly, to the laws specified in the Annex or to actions based thereon or resulting there from, shall be recognized or be enforceable in any manner. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;htki &uuml;hendusev&auml;lise kohtu otsust ega &uuml;htki &uuml;hendusest v&auml;ljaspool asuva haldusasutuse otsust, mis otseselt v&otilde;i kaudselt j&otilde;ustavad lisas nimetatud seadusi v&otilde;i neil p&otilde;hinevaid v&otilde;i neist tulenevaid meetmeid, ei tunnustata ega p&ouml;&ouml;rata t&auml;itmisele &uuml;helgi viisil. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> No person referred to in Article 11 shall comply, whether directly or through a subsidiary or other intermediary person, actively or by deliberate omission, with any requirement or prohibition, including requests of foreign courts, based on or resulting, directly or indirectly, from the laws specified in the Annex or from actions based thereon or resulting therefrom. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;kski artiklis 11 nimetatud isik ei t&auml;ida vahetult ega oma t&uuml;tarettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i muu vahendusisiku kaudu tegutsedes v&otilde;i tahtlikult tegutsemata j&auml;ttes mingeid n&otilde;udeid ega keelde, sealhulgas &uuml;hendusev&auml;liste kohtute n&otilde;udeid, mis otseselt v&otilde;i kaudselt p&otilde;hinevad lisas m&auml;&auml;ratletud seadustel v&otilde;i neil p&otilde;hinevatel v&otilde;i neist tulenevatel toimingutel. </eesti>
<inglise> Persons may be authorized, in accordance with the procedures provided in Articles 7 and 8, to comply fully or partially to the extent that non-compliance would seriously damage their interests or those of the Community. </inglise>
<eesti> Isikutele v&otilde;ib artiklites 7 ja 8 s&auml;testatud korras anda loa neid seadusi t&auml;ielikult v&otilde;i osaliselt t&auml;ita niiv&otilde;rd, kuiv&otilde;rd mittet&auml;itmine kahjustaks oluliselt nende v&otilde;i &uuml;henduse huve. </eesti>
<inglise> The criteria for the application of this provision shall be established in accordance with the procedure set out in Article 8. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva s&auml;tte kohaldamise kriteeriumid kehtestatakse artiklis 8 s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise> When there is sufficient evidence that non-compliance would cause serious damage to a natural or legal person, the Commission shall expeditiously submit to the committee referred to in Article 8 a draft of the appropriate measures to be taken under the terms of the Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui on piisavalt t&otilde;endeid, et mittet&auml;itmine v&otilde;iks p&otilde;hjustada f&uuml;&uuml;silisele v&otilde;i juriidilisele isikule olulist kahju, esitab komisjon viivitamata artiklis 8 nimetatud komiteele vastavalt k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse tingimustele v&otilde;etavate asjakohaste meetmete eeln&otilde;u. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> Any person referred to in Article 11, who is engaging in an activity referred to in Article 1 shall be entitled to recover any damages, including legal costs, caused to that person by the application of the laws specified in the Annex or by actions based thereon or resulting therefrom. </inglise>
<eesti> Igal artiklis 11 nimetatud isikul, kes tegutseb artiklis 1 nimetatud valdkondades, on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda selliste kahjude, sealhulgas kohtukulude, h&uuml;vitamist, mida k&otilde;nealusele isikule on p&otilde;hjustanud lisas nimetatud seaduste v&otilde;i neil p&otilde;hinevate v&otilde;i neist tulenevate meetmete kohaldamine. </eesti>
<inglise> Such recovery may be obtained from the natural or legal person or any other entity causing the damages or from any person acting on its behalf or intermediary. </inglise>
<eesti> Kahjusid v&otilde;ib sisse n&otilde;uda f&uuml;&uuml;siliselt v&otilde;i juriidiliselt isikult v&otilde;i muult kahju p&otilde;hjustanud &uuml;ksuselt v&otilde;i mis tahes isikult, kes tegutseb nende nimel v&otilde;i nende vahendajana. </eesti>
<inglise> The Brussels Convention of 27 September 1968 on jurisdiction and the enforcement of judgments in civil and commercial matters shall apply to proceedings brought and judgments given under this Article. </inglise>
<eesti> Vastavalt k&auml;esolevale artiklile algatatud menetluste ja tehtud otsuste suhtes kohaldatakse 27. septembri 1968. aasta Br&uuml;sseli konventsiooni kohtualluvuse ja kohtuotsuste t&auml;itmise kohta tsiviil- ja kaubandusasjades. </eesti>
<inglise> Recovery may be obtained on the basis of the provisions of Sections 2 to 6 of Title II of that Convention, as well as, in accordance with Article 57 (3) of that Convention, through judicial proceedings instituted in the Courts of any Member State where that person, entity, person acting on its behalf or intermediary holds assets. </inglise>
<eesti> Kahjude h&uuml;vitamist v&otilde;ib taotleda k&otilde;nealuse konventsiooni II jaotise jagude 2 - 6 s&auml;tete alusel, samuti vastavalt k&otilde;nelause konventsiooni artikli 57 l&otilde;ikele 3 iga liikmesriigi kohtute algatatud kohtumenetluse kaudu, kus sel isikul, &uuml;ksusel, tema nimel tegutseval isikul v&otilde;i vahendajal on vara. </eesti>
<inglise> Without prejudice to other means available and in accordance with applicable law, the recovery could take the form of seizure and sale of assets held by those persons, entities, persons acting on their behalf or intermediaries within the Community, including shares held in a legal person incorporated within the Community. </inglise>
<eesti> Koosk&otilde;las kohaldatava seadusega v&otilde;ib kahjude sissen&otilde;udmine toimuda nende isikute, &uuml;ksuste, nende nimel tegutsevate isikute v&otilde;i vahendajate &uuml;henduses oleva vara, sealhulgas &uuml;henduses registreeritud juriidilise isiku aktsiate v&otilde;i osade konfiskeerimise ja m&uuml;&uuml;mise vormis ilma et see piiraks muude asjakohaste vahendite kasutamist. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 7 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 7 </eesti>
<inglise> For the implementation of this Regulation the Commission shall: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse rakendamisel peab komisjon: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) inform the European Parliament and the Council immediately and fully of the effects of the laws, regulations and other legislative instruments and ensuing actions mentioned in Article 1, on the basis of the information obtained under this Regulation, and make regularly a full public report thereon; </inglise>
